# Web Map Application

This project is a web map application built using HTML, CSS, and the Leaflet library. The application allows users to explore maps,
retrieve weather data for cities, find popular places, and retrieve country details using various APIs.

## Features

- Display maps using the Leaflet library.
- Retrieve current weather data for cities using the Weatherbit API.
- Find and display popular places using the OpenCageData API.
- Retrieve country details using the REST Countries API.
- Interactive user interface with search functionalities.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository: `git clone <repository-url>`
2. Open the `index.html` file in a web browser.

## Usage

- Enter a city name and click "Search Weather" to retrieve and display current weather data.
- Click "Search popular Place" to find and display popular places in the provided city.
- Enter a country name in the "Country name" input and click "Search Country" to retrieve and display country details.

## APIs Used

- [Weatherbit API](https://www.weatherbit.io/api) - For retrieving weather data.
- [OpenCageData API](https://opencagedata.com/api) - For finding popular places.
- [REST Countries API](https://restcountries.com/) - For retrieving country details.

## Acknowledgments

- [Leaflet](https://leafletjs.com/) - An open-source JavaScript library for interactive maps.
- [Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/) - For providing images used in the project.
